		"description": "<p>A Bolt of Slaying is a magic weapon meant to slay a particular kind of creature. Some are more focused than others; for example, there are both Bolts of Dragon Slaying and Bolts of Blue Dragon Slaying. If a creature belonging to the type, race, or group associated with a bolt of slaying takes damage from the bolt, the creature must make a DC 17 Constitution saving throw, taking an extra 6d10 piercing damage on a failed save, or half as much extra damage on a successful one.</p>\n<p>Once a Bolt of Slaying deals its extra damage to a creature, it becomes a nonmagical bolt.</p>",
